                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d223">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/5491: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1"
                            type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-08-20T10:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 20, 1932—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 20—5:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>978. Following from American Consul General at Mukden: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“August 19, 10 a.m. Referring to my despatch of August 9th, the local
                            spokesman of Japanese military headquarters yesterday reported that 24
                            delegates of the people of Jehol, each representing a different
                            district, had called upon Japanese headquarters at Chinchow to express
                            the hope that Japanese troops be sent to suppress banditry in Jehol.</p>
                        <p>Disorder continues most active throughout South Manchuria. On the 16th
                            bandits destroyed tracks and bridges on Kirin-Tunhua line 10 miles east
                            of Kirin resulting in derailment of one train and several days’
                            suspension of traffic. On the same day a train was wrecked and attacked
                            on the Kirin-Hailung line.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
